Ministry of Defense: Shahed interceptions doubled, enemy loses up to 254 fighters per kilometer of advance
Ministry of Defense of Ukraine released a report on the implementation of the Air-Land-Economy strategy: protect the sky, stop the enemy on the ground, and maximize exhaustion of the adversary's economy. The main goal is to force the enemy to peace through the strength of Ukraine.
Sky Defense
the percentage of Shahed interceptions by interceptor drones increased twofold over the last 4 months – despite Moscow increasing their numbers by 35% monthly;
interceptor drone supplies increased 2.6 times over the same period;
strategic goal: stable 95% interception rate of air targets;
begun testing of cheap interceptor rockets to shoot down Shaheds. Task by autumn: scale production tenfold.
Private Air Defense
27 enterprises from Kharkiv, Odesa, Kyiv, Zaporizhzhia, Poltava, Zakarpattia and other regions joined the experimental project;
air defense groups from two enterprises have already destroyed about 20 enemy Shaheds and reconnaissance drones;
confirmed interception of a reactive Shahed in Kharkiv region.
🇷🇺
Moscow's losses on the front
In April, 35,203 Russian servicemen were killed or seriously wounded; in March – 35,351; in December – 34,544. All figures verified through the eBali system. If in October 2024 Moscow was losing 67 servicemen per 1 km² of advance, then in January – 165, in February – 244, in March – 254, in April – 179. Among key factors: Starlink cutoff for Moscow in February 2026 and ac

